column1: For arrival series, the country of residence is the country where a person last lived for 12 months or more (country of last permanent residence).
For permanent and long-term departure series, the country of residence is the country where a person intends to live for the next 12 months or more (country of next permanent residence).
The United Kingdom also includes the Channel Islands and the Isle of Man.

For visitor departure series, the country of residence is the country where the visitor last lived for 12 months or more. Before July 2013, it was the country where the visitor next intended to live for 12 months or more.
For detailed metadata about countries used in International Travel and Migration statistics, see DataInfo+. http://ow.ly/Mm9ba
Prior to August 2016 visitor departures data was derived from a sample of records and hence may have contained sample error.
From August 2016 visitor departures country of residence is captured from matched visitor arrivals records and may contain matching error and affect comparability to previous periods.
Imputation of 'country of residence' for visitor arrivals who have not stated a response on their arrival card, occurred from August 2016 to October 2018.
Observed changes in travel from a country may be partly due to these methodology changes.
The country name Swaziland changed to Eswatini from October 2018.
The country name Czech Republic changed to Czechia from Oct 2018.
